'''Interior of the Heiden'''

The coffered lattice ceiling of the heiden is decorated with polychrome paintings of animals, plants, and human figures. Only during the first three days of the New Year, a goma altar is set up in front of the main hall doors within the heiden, where goma fire rituals are performed. During these rituals, prayers are offered by holding amulets and votive items directly over the sacred flames.
<gallery>
File:Heiden of Taka-jinja shrine.JPG|Interior of the Heiden
