File:Heiden of Taka-jinja shrine 2.JPG|Paintings on the lattice ceiling of the Heiden<br/>The rear of the photo shows the Heiden entrance.
File:Gomadan of Taka-jinja shrine.JPG|Goma altar at Taka Shrine<br/>Only during the New Year period, a tree called “Nodeppō” is used as goma sticks for the ritual.
</gallery>

'''Interior of the Worship Hall'''

Inside the worship hall are housed items such as an ema depicting “Izanagi-no-Mikoto and Izanami-no-Mikoto,” paintings of hawks, and a plaque reading “Protection of the State,” dedicated in Meiji 38 to commemorate the {{ill|lt=Siege of Port Arthur|Q210800|WD=Q210800|lt=Fall of Port Arthur|1=Siege of Port Arthur}} during the Russo-Japanese War.
