=== Subsidiary and Branch Shrines ===
* Yasaka-Inari Shrine
*: The shrine building reuses the former main hall of Taka Shrine, and within it are enshrined Yasaka Shrine and Inari Shrine. Yasaka Shrine was formerly called Gozu Tennō Shrine and had been located in the Jō-no-uchi area, the present location. According to *Ōsōshi*, the sacred object of Yasaka Shrine measures 7 sun in length. Inari Shrine was formerly located in the Oinari area southeast of the current site and was later enshrined together with Yasaka Shrine.
*: On the east side of the shrine building are a sacred cedar tree, Raijin Shrine, and a stone monument of Aomasa Daigongen (Aomasa Shrine).
* Raijin Shrine
*: The sacred object is recorded as measuring 7 sun in length.
* Aomasa Daigongen (Aomasa Shrine) Stone Monument
*: The enshrined deities are Amaterasu Ōmikami, Tsukuyomi-no-Kami, and Ame-no-Minakanushi-no-Kami. It was transferred from {{ill|lt=Aomasa Shrine|Q11662833|WD=Q11662833|1=Aoso Shrine}} in Iwakiri, Miyagino Ward, Sendai City, Miyagi Prefecture.

